SIMPLE: croconic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Croconic
<hw>Cro*con"ic</hw> <pr>(kr?-k?n"?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/<?/<?/<?/ saffron.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
resembling saffron; having the color of saffron; <as>as,
<ex>croconic</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from, croconic
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 347 --></p>

<p><cs><col><b>Croconic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a yellow
crystalline substance, <chform>C5O3(OH)2</chform>, obtained from
potassium carboxide, rhodizonic acid, and various phenol and quinone
derivatives of benzene, and forming yellow or orange colored
salts.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crocose</ent>⟦br⟧
